	return (
 	// JSX (html + javascript)
	)
}			


****It should return only one parent div

JSX: html + js

to diffentiate js we user { }
ex:
return (
      <div>
        Test component
        { console.log(30) }
      </div>
    )


render() will be called each and every time whenever the state updated.

we'll take this advantage and check the data from state conditionally.


we defined state object with city, country properties as null values
we defined input fields
we defined handlers to recieve the entered data

we updated the state's city, county object with setState({})

